  <body>
    <section name="Add date to document type">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to add a date field to a document type.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=450;
    bottompx=610;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M9/inars/add_date_to_documenttype.png" alt='Add date to documenttype screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
    <p>
      Adding mandatory date field snp:upcoming_date with caption 'Upcoming date'
      to document type `upcoming'.
     </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    Ensure that you have the document type in <a href='../concepts/edit_mode.html'>edit mode</a>.
    In the <a href='../concepts/field_type_menu.html'>field type menu</a>,
    choose 'Date'. A new date field appears as part of the document type.
    The <span href='../concepts/field_properties_overview.html'>field properties overview</span>
    of the new field also appears. Define at least the following properties:
   </p>
   <ul>
    <li>
     <a href='./fieldcaption.html'>Define a caption for the new field</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
     Also <a href='./naming_a_field.html'>define a name</a> for it.
    </li>
    <li>
     And decide if it should be <a href='./mandatory_or_optional.html'>mandatory or optional</a>.
    </li>
   </ul>

